        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1958",
        "content": "The heat into which he has been continually putting himself; and the distracted and impetuous manner in which he has been diving, day and night, among papers and books; to say nothing of the immense number of letters he has written me between this house and mr Wickfield's, and often across the table when he has been sitting opposite, and might much more easily have spoken; is quite extraordinary.'",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-normal_e-low",
