        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1958",
        "content": "'I am happy to say, Miss Wickfield,' pursued Traddles, at once with great delicacy and with great earnestness, 'that in your absence mr Wickfield has considerably improved.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
