        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1958",
        "content": "mr Wickfield, being so weak and helpless in his hands as to pay you, afterwards, several sums of interest on a pretended principal which he knew did not exist, made himself, unhappily, a party to the fraud.'",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
